name: Hubble Celebrates its 31st anniversary with a magnificent view of AG Carinae
description:
The star, called AG Carinae, is surrounded by an expanding shell of gas and dust. The nebula is about five light-years wide, which equals the distance from here to our nearest star, Alpha Centauri.

Name:	AG Carinae, V* AG Car
Type:	Milky Way : Star : Type : Wolf-Rayet
Distance:	15000 light years
Constellation:	Carina
Category:	Anniversary Stars

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.
